1. To Which Events Can You Listen?
   Section 3, Lecture 41
   In the last lecture, we saw that you can react to the onClick event - but to which other events can you listen?
   You can find a list of supported events here: https://reactjs.org/docs/events.html#supported-events


2. Arrow functions let us use this keyword in them, in normal functions we can't use it.

3. Whenever we change the rendered component using a button or something the whole render() function runs again 
   and not just the return part.

4. Use source maps and breakpoints and debugger to fix logical errors.